 <div class="articlecontent">
<h1>Tesco puts security tags on milk after surge in &#39;thefts&#39; in cost of living crisis</h1>
<div>
<div>
 <span class="partner">
 <a  href="https://metro.co.uk/"  title="metro logo"><img alt="Metro logo" src="//img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/BB1d0ujN.img?h=17&amp;w=0&amp;m=6&amp;q=60&amp;u=t&amp;o=t&amp;l=f&amp;f=png" title="Metro logo" /> Metro</a>
 </span>
 <span>
 <span class="time">22/11/2022</span>
         <span class="authorname-txt" 
              
              
              >
                <span class="truncate" >Josh Milton</span>
        </span>

                </span>
            </div>
        </div>

 <div class="richtext"  data-aop="articlebody">
 
 <span class="storyimage fullwidth inlineimage"  data-aop="image">
<span class="image" data-attrib="Provided by Metro" data-caption="Tesco said the cartons were down to ‘human error’ amid an increase in thefts (Picture: Greg Martin / Cornwall Live)" >
 <img alt="Tesco said the cartons were down to ‘human error’ amid an increase in thefts (Picture: Greg Martin / Cornwall Live)" height="199" src="//img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AA14oQeX.img?h=199&amp;w=300&amp;m=6&amp;q=60&amp;o=f&amp;l=f" width="300" />
</span>
<span class="caption truncate">
 <span class="attribution">&#169; Provided by Metro</span>
 Tesco said the cartons were down to ‘human error’ amid an increase in thefts (Picture: Greg Martin / Cornwall Live)
</span>
</span>
    <p class="">The stark extent of the<a href="https://metro.co.uk/tag/cost-of-living/"> cost-of-living </a>crisis has been laid bare as some pints of milk were spotted in a <a href="https://metro.co.uk/tag/tesco/">Tesco</a> supermarket with security tags on them amid a spike of ‘thefts’.</p>    <p class="">As the price of daily essentials such as tea bags and sugar swell, shoppers were stunned to see milk containers treated like expensive alcohol bottles. </p>    <p class="">The Tesco Extra in Pool, a village in west Cornwall, has seen a wave of milk thefts as inflation continues to gnaw at people’s grocery budgets. </p>    <p class="">A shopper photographed at least three milk bottles in the supermarket with individual security tags that have to be removed by cashiers. </p>    <p class="">A Tesco staffer reportedly told a shopper the pints were tagged because of thefts, though a spokesperson for the supermarket said tagging milk is ‘not’ policy.</p>    <p class="">They told <strong><a href="https://www.cornwalllive.com/whats-on/shopping/milk-containers-security-tagged-cornwall-7847613">CornwallLive</a></strong>: ‘I couldn’t believe it at first and thought it was some kind of joke or a mistake but I overheard a member of staff tell a customer that there had been a lot of thefts of milk and this was their way of trying to stop it.’</p>    
 <span class="storyimage fullwidth inlineimage"  data-aop="image">
<span class="image" data-attrib="Provided by Metro" data-caption="At least three milk containers had been clipped with security tags (Picture: Greg Martin / Cornwall Live)" >
 <img alt="At least three milk containers had been clipped with security tags (Picture: Greg Martin / Cornwall Live)" height="225" src="//img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AA14p7y0.img?h=225&amp;w=300&amp;m=6&amp;q=60&amp;o=f&amp;l=f" width="300" />
</span>
<span class="caption truncate">
 <span class="attribution">&#169; Provided by Metro</span>
 At least three milk containers had been clipped with security tags (Picture: Greg Martin / Cornwall Live)
</span>
</span>
    <p class="">And a pint of milk certainly isn’t the only go-to grocery that supermarkets have had to tag in recent months. </p>    <p class="">Other shoppers up and down the UK have seen grocers step up security by tagging everything from cheese and Lurpak spreadable butter to baby milk.</p>    <p class="">Supermarkets often say the reason is down to shoplifting, but many of the tagged products have seen their price tags increase in recent months.</p>    <p class="">At one point in September – when inflation stood at 10.1% – the price of milk was more expensive than petrol at the pump in some supermarkets. </p>    <p class="">Some shops sold single pints for as much as £1.05, or about £1.85 per litre when fuel was about 191p a lire to around 149p in some areas, per <a href="https://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/uk-news/soaring-price-milk-make-more-25050508">Wales Online</a>.</p>    <p class="">According to data from the Office for National Statistics, milk has been on an upward trend since the 1970s, </p>    <p class="">The average price for a pint of pasteurised milk was 46p in January this year but has since risen 41% to 65p as of October, the agency found.</p>    
 <span class="storyimage fullwidth inlineimage"  data-aop="image">
<span class="image" data-attrib="Provided by Metro" data-caption="Blocks of cheese were spotted earlier this year with beefed-up security (Picture: @CharIieBennett/@Celeste_Tam42/Twitter)" >
 <img alt="Blocks of cheese were spotted earlier this year with beefed-up security (Picture: @CharIieBennett/@Celeste_Tam42/Twitter)" height="197" src="//img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AAZAc9W.img?h=197&amp;w=300&amp;m=6&amp;q=60&amp;o=f&amp;l=f" width="300" />
</span>
<span class="caption truncate">
 <span class="attribution">&#169; Provided by Metro</span>
 Blocks of cheese were spotted earlier this year with beefed-up security (Picture: @CharIieBennett/@Celeste_Tam42/Twitter)
</span>
</span>
    
 <span class="storyimage fullwidth inlineimage"  data-aop="image">
<span class="image" data-attrib="Provided by Metro" data-caption="A number of shops have attached security precautions to products like they do alcohol (Picture: Getty Images)" >
 <img alt="A number of shops have attached security precautions to products like they do alcohol (Picture: Getty Images)" height="200" src="//img-s-msn-com.akamaized.net/tenant/amp/entityid/AA14p2Zb.img?h=200&amp;w=300&amp;m=6&amp;q=60&amp;o=f&amp;l=f" width="300" />
</span>
<span class="caption truncate">
 <span class="attribution">&#169; Provided by Metro</span>
 A number of shops have attached security precautions to products like they do alcohol (Picture: Getty Images)
</span>
</span>
    <p class="">The UK’s cost of living crisis has only deepened since, with consumer prices surging 11.1% from a year earlier, the highest in more than 40 years.</p>    <p class="">Fuel was among the driving forces for the increase that was higher than expected.</p>    <p class="">On a month-to-month basis, the <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://www.ons.gov.uk/economy/inflationandpriceindices/bulletins/consumerpriceinflation/latest">Consumer Prices Index</a> (the most widely used measure of inflation) rose 2% from September.</p>    <p class="">Even those who make milk are feeling the pinch. A survey of arable and dairy members by the <a href="https://www.nfuonline.com/updates-and-information/rising-costs-government-needs-to-assess-impacts-on-farming/">National Farming Union </a>found three in four are considering stopping milk altogether by 2024.</p>    <p class="">A Tesco spokesperson told Metro.co.uk: ‘We do not have a policy to place security tags on fresh milk. </p>    <p class="">‘A very small amount of milk was incorrectly tagged today in our Redruth Extra store and these tags have now been removed. We’re sorry for any inconvenience caused.’</p>                <p class=""><strong><strong><strong>Get in touch with our news team by emailing us at <a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="mailto:webnews@metro.co.uk">webnews@metro.co.uk</a>.</strong></strong></strong></p>    <p class=""><strong>For more stories like this, </strong><a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="https://metro.co.uk/news/"><strong>check our news page</strong></a>.</p> <p>Get your need-to-know latest news, feel-good stories, analysis and more by signing up to <a href="https://metro.co.uk/newsletters/?ito=msn_newsletter-cta_news&signup-source=msn-text-cta">Metro's News Updates newsletter</a></p>
</div>
 </div>

 

